[{"id": "7383c3d6-ea86-479a-bf0f-178392e6ae86", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: Hi. i was just given early beta access to lagoon. where should I start?\nASSISTANT: Hey, welcome in!\n\nCouple quick questions to point you in the right direction:\n\n1. **What are you running it on?** Windows installer is the smoothest path \u2014 grab LagoonSetup.exe from the GitHub releases, make sure you have Python 3.10+, and it'll walk you through the rest. Mac/Linux means cloning the repo and running setup.py manually.\n\n2. **Do you already have an AI setup you like?** If you've got Ollama running locally, you're golden \u2014 Lagoon will find it automatically, no keys needed. If you want cloud models, Venice.ai and Together.ai are your options. You'll need API keys from whichever you pick.\n\nOnce you're in, the flow is: pick a model from the dropdown at the top, then either load a character from the sidebar or hit \"New Character\" to build your own. The character config has all the usual stuff \u2014 system prompt, personality, scenario, first message, lorebook, author's note.\n\nWhat's your setup looking like? Happy to walk through whichever path fits.", "embedding": [-0.019790733233094215, -0.10392832010984421, 0.01694156974554062, -0.01316108275204897, -0.0200974028557539, -0.05365560203790665, -0.02196943201124668, 0.0009313102927990258, -0.029825681820511818, -0.048862699419260025, 0.02106633596122265, -0.11273536831140518, 0.014975047670304775, -0.02746233344078064, 0.05991094559431076, 0.0618944950401783, 0.059135839343070984, -0.049138810485601425, -0.0015043758321553469, 0.003512432100251317, -0.005005133803933859, 0.03254659101366997, -0.026008358225226402, -0.008870971389114857, -0.01018898468464613, 0.012306030839681625, 0.054164204746484756, -0.008101403713226318, -0.05554019287228584, -0.004062437918037176, -0.02671973779797554, -0.01930161751806736, 0.02516237460076809, -0.027885563671588898, 0.14155903458595276, -0.003969915211200714, 0.007834608666598797, -0.